		<pubDate>Sun, 30 Jan 2011 03:00:32 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>John</dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[Time Saving Tool]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[evernote]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://tipsandtech.com/?p=263</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[Are you organizationally challenged? Evernote may be the answer to finally keep you organized! If you ever visited my office pre-2011 you know that I was addicted to sticky note.   I would write on them when listening to my phone messages,  when I got an email I needed to take action on, if made [...]]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p></p><p><a href="http://tipsandtech.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/images-8.jpg"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-264" title="Evernote Logo" src="http://tipsandtech.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/images-8.jpg" alt="" width="204" height="204" /></a>Are you organizationally challenged?</p>
<p><a href="http://evernote.com/" target="_blank">Evernote</a> may be the answer to finally keep you organized!</p>
<p>If you ever visited my office pre-2011 you know that I was addicted to sticky note.   I would write on them when listening to my phone messages,  when I got an email I needed to take action on, if made a commitment to help someone with something in the future, or if I just had an awesome idea (like creating TichsandTech.com.)  I had sticky notes all over my desk.  When I had to pull a new stack out of my drawer and I started using a different color, that was my cue to finish all the things on the notes of the previous color.</p>
<p>Not a great system!</p>
<p>In 2011 I have been making every effort to work as paperless as possible and you can definitely tell it is working.  If you saw my desk today compared to only a few months ago, there are no sticky notes anywhere!  One of the tools I have been using that is helping me keep my notes organized is Evernote.</p>
<p>I use the <a href="https://chrome.google.com/webstore/detail/pioclpoplcdbaefihamjohnefbikjilc" target="_blank">Google Chrome Extension </a>to save webclips and pages directly to Evernote, plus I have been making notes on my phone and on my desktop and every note syncs on every device. <img src='http://tipsandtech.com/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif' alt=':)' class='wp-smiley' /> </p>
<p>Check out this great blog post, <a href="http://p1fran.com/2011/01/forever-evernote/" target="_blank">Forever Evernote</a> by <a href="http://twitter.com/#!/ProfessionalOne" target="_blank">@ProfessionalOne</a> for more about Evernote and some specific examples of how a REALTOR® uses Evernote is his business daily.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
