		<title>Facebook tips | Send status updates to specific friends</title>
		<link>http://tipsandtech.com/facebook-tips-send-status-updates-to-specific-friends/</link>
		<comments>http://tipsandtech.com/facebook-tips-send-status-updates-to-specific-friends/#comments</comments>
		<pubDate>Fri, 28 Jan 2011 03:31:10 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>John</dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[Facebook]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[facebook]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://tipsandtech.com/?p=250</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[Ever wonder how you can send a status update, post a link or post a photo in Facebook, but only have it display to a specific set of friends? This is possible and today you are going to learn just how easy this awesome feature is to use. I commonly want post a joke or [...]]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p></p><p style="text-align: left;">
<img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-251" title="choose who sees your status updates" src="http://tipsandtech.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/images-3.jpg" alt="" width="236" height="157" /></p>
<p style="text-align: left;">Ever wonder how you can send a status update, post a link or post a photo in Facebook, but only have it display to a specific set of friends?</p>
<p style="text-align: left;">This is possible and today you are going to learn just how easy this awesome feature is to use.</p>
<p style="text-align: left;">I commonly want post a joke or a funny video to Facebook, but only want my REALTOR® friends to see it.  The first step is sorting your friends into lists.  <a href="http://tipsandtech.com/managing-facebook-with-friend-lists/" target="_blank">We talked about this earlier in the month.</a></p>
<p style="text-align: left;">Hopefully you know how to post to Facebook!  at the top of your newsfeed you know that you simply enter your status update, upload your photo or ad your link.  What you may not have ever noticed, but has always been there is the little &#8220;padlock&#8221; icon.</p>
<p style="text-align: left;"><img class="size-full wp-image-255 aligncenter" title="1-27-2011 9-11-13 PM" src="http://tipsandtech.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/1-27-2011-9-11-13-PM1.png" alt="" width="509" height="138" /></p>
<p style="text-align: left;">This padlock holds the secret we are looking for today.  When you click on it, you have a few options fro who will receive your update.</p>
<p style="text-align: left;"><a href="http://tipsandtech.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/1-27-2011-9-17-56-PM.png"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-256" title="1-27-2011 9-17-56 PM" src="http://tipsandtech.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/1-27-2011-9-17-56-PM.png" alt="" width="196" height="125" /></a>&#8220;Customize&#8221; is the choice you are looking for.  When you click this option a new window appears that allows you to choose specific people to make this particular post visible to. <em>Note: At this point you could also choose who to HIDE this post from, but we&#8217;re not talking about that today!</em></p>
<p style="text-align: left;"><a style="font-style: italic;" href="http://tipsandtech.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/1-27-2011-9-20-51-PM.png"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-257" title="1-27-2011 9-20-51 PM" src="http://tipsandtech.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/1-27-2011-9-20-51-PM.png" alt="" width="528" height="263" /></a>Once you choose the &#8220;Specific People&#8221; option, you can start typing any of your friends by name to specifically choose individuals who will only be able to see the post.  My favorite option here is to enter the name of one of my FRIEND LISTS.</p>
<p style="text-align: left;"><a href="http://tipsandtech.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/1-27-2011-9-27-15-PM.png"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-258" title="1-27-2011 9-27-15 PM" src="http://tipsandtech.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/1-27-2011-9-27-15-PM.png" alt="" width="326" height="133" /></a>This will only post this particular message to this group of friends, it won&#8217;t show up on anyone else&#8217;s newsfeed!</p>
]]></content:encoded>
			<wfw:commentRss>http://tipsandtech.com/facebook-tips-send-status-updates-to-specific-friends/feed/</wfw:commentRss>
