		</item>
		<item>
		<title>Managing Facebook with friend lists</title>
		<link>http://tipsandtech.com/managing-facebook-with-friend-lists/</link>
		<comments>http://tipsandtech.com/managing-facebook-with-friend-lists/#comments</comments>
		<pubDate>Sun, 09 Jan 2011 23:37:08 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>John</dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[Facebook]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Time Saving Tool]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[facebook]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[friends lists]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://tipsandtech.com/?p=225</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[Do you use Facebook everyday and find it difficult to find the information that is most important to you?  Or do you find yourself not using it everyday because you&#8217;re getting information overload?  I have an easy way to manage all your friends so you can easily navigate to the posts and pictures from the [...]]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p></p><p><a href="http://tipsandtech.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/Untitled-1.jpg"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-226" title="Facebook friend lists" src="http://tipsandtech.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/Untitled-1.jpg" alt="managing facebook with lists" width="201" height="229" /></a>Do you use Facebook everyday and find it difficult to find the information that is most important to you?  Or do you find yourself not using it everyday because you&#8217;re getting information overload?  I have an easy way to manage all your friends so you can easily navigate to the posts and pictures from the people most important to you.</p>
<p>We can easily manage your friends and their information with friends lists.</p>
<p>When you login to Facebook each time, you are automatically shown your newsfeed.  This does NOT include all the posts and pictures your friends have posted to Facebook.  I personally have over 500 Facebook friends and am not always interested in what all 500 of my friends are doing on a daily basis.  I just want to see what my top 100 or so friends are up to, so we will create a friends list.</p>
<p><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-227" title="1-9-2011 4-42-07 PM" src="http://tipsandtech.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/1-9-2011-4-42-07-PM.jpg" alt="managing facebook with lists" width="235" height="250" /></p>
<p>To create a friend list, start by going to your menu at the top right of your Facebook page and click &#8220;Account,&#8221; the &#8220;Edit Friends.&#8221;</p>
<p>You should now have a list of all your friends.  at the top right of this page, you will see a button titled &#8221; Create List&#8221;</p>
<p><a href="http://tipsandtech.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/1-9-2011-4-45-28-PM.jpg"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-228" title="1-9-2011 4-45-28 PM" src="http://tipsandtech.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/1-9-2011-4-45-28-PM.jpg" alt="" width="113" height="36" /></a></p>
<p>By clicking this button, a window will popup with all of your friends in the window.</p>
<p><a href="http://tipsandtech.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/1-9-2011-4-47-39-PM.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-229 alignleft" title="1-9-2011 4-47-39 PM" src="http://tipsandtech.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/1-9-2011-4-47-39-PM.jpg" alt="managing facebook with lists" width="354" height="338" /></a>Here you need to give your list a name and choose all the friends you would like to be in this particular list.</p>
<p>When you have all your friends chosen for the list, click the  &#8221;Create List&#8221; button at the bottom of the popup window.</p>
<p><img class="alignleft size-medium wp-image-232" title="1-9-2011 4-58-47 PM" src="http://tipsandtech.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/1-9-2011-4-58-47-PM-300x145.jpg" alt="managing facebook with lists" width="300" height="145" /></p>
<p>You can create as many lists as you want and even add each friend to more than one list.  For example, I have 6 different lists.  Some people are on two or three lists so I can pull up a list and they would show up in each group.  Back on the &#8220;Edit Friends&#8221; page you can see which list each friend is on, by moving your mouse to right side of each friends box to find the invisible &#8220;Edit List&#8221; button.</p>
<p><img class="size-full wp-image-235 alignright" title="1-9-2011 5-02-02 PM" src="http://tipsandtech.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/1-9-2011-5-02-02-PM.jpg" alt="managing facebook with lists" width="139" height="167" /></p>
<p>Once your lists are created, you can edit which lists your friends are associated with right here by click on this once invisible button.</p>
<p><strong>NOW&#8230;. How does this make your daily Facebook experience easier?</strong></p>
<p><img class="alignleft size-medium wp-image-238" title="1-9-2011 5-07-41 PM" src="http://tipsandtech.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/1-9-2011-5-07-41-PM-230x300.jpg" alt="managing facebook with lists" width="230" height="300" /></p>
<p>When I login to Facebook I immediately go to the &#8220;Most Recent&#8221; link above your Newsfeed.  This will bring a list of all your friends lists up so you can pick and choose whose information you want to read through right now.</p>
<p><strong>This even works on my Iphone!  Let me show you how.</strong></p>
<p>When I open Facebook on my phone, I immediately click on the button at to top right.  This button will be labeled either &#8220;Live Feed&#8221; or it will be the Friend List you are currently viewing.</p>
<div id="attachment_240" class="wp-caption alignright" style="width: 229px">
	<a href="http://tipsandtech.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/1-9-2011-5-16-49-PM.png"><img class="size-medium wp-image-240  " title="1-9-2011 5-16-49 PM" src="http://tipsandtech.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/1-9-2011-5-16-49-PM-229x300.png" alt="managing facebook with lists" width="229" height="300" /></a>
	<p class="wp-caption-text">Facebook Lists on the Iphone</p>
</div>
<p>When you click on this button, you will have the opportunity to change the list you are currently viewing.</p>
<p>This save me time everyday, because I use my phone for Facebook probably 80% of my total Facebook time.   I can easily change to the list I want to read.  I made a list called &#8220;My Favorites&#8221; and have included all my favorite friends to this list so I can find the posts from the friends and family that are most important to me.</p>
<p>If I decide I want to see another list, simply change lists, and you can see what a completely different group of people is up to in their daily lives.</p>
<p>My next post will be about how you can send pictures, links or status updates to specific people, or even to a specific Friends List!</p>
<p>Do you have a Facebook specific topic you&#8217;d like me to write about?</p>
]]></content:encoded>
			<wfw:commentRss>http://tipsandtech.com/managing-facebook-with-friend-lists/feed/</wfw:commentRss>
		<slash:comments />
		</item>
		<item>
		<title>Want an simple online newsletter… try Tiny Letter</title>
		<link>http://tipsandtech.com/want-an-simple-online-newsletter-try-tiny-letter/</link>
		<comments>http://tipsandtech.com/want-an-simple-online-newsletter-try-tiny-letter/#comments</comments>
		<pubDate>Wed, 05 Jan 2011 02:30:43 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>John</dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[Prospecting]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[online newsletter]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[tiny letter]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://tipsandtech.com/?p=209</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[If you have been looking for a super simple online email newsletter system, there is nothing simpler than TinyLetter.com. Once you complete the easy registration process, completing your first newsletter is as simple as the image to the right. But first, before you write your first newsletter, you need to add some contacts.  Adding contacts [...]]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p></p><p><a href="http://tipsandtech.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/1-4-2011-7-36-09-PM.png"><img class="size-full wp-image-210 alignleft" title="1-4-2011 7-36-09 PM" src="http://tipsandtech.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/1-4-2011-7-36-09-PM.png" alt="" width="123" height="73" /></a>If you have been looking for a super simple online email newsletter system, there is nothing simpler than<a href="http://TinyLetter.com" target="_blank"> TinyLetter.com</a>.</p>
<p><img class="size-full wp-image-211 alignright" title="1-4-2011 7-57-13 PM" src="http://tipsandtech.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/1-4-2011-7-57-13-PM.png" alt="" width="198" height="166" /></p>
<p>Once you complete the easy registration process, completing your first newsletter is as simple as the image to the right.</p>
<p>But first, before you write your first newsletter, you need to add some contacts.  Adding contacts is not difficult.  You can either, manually enter your contacts, or if you export them form your contact manager as a Comma Delimited file, you can copy and paste the entire list right in without too much effort.  One of the cool features in your newsletter is an automatic UNSUBSCRIBE link.  When a contact who wishes to unsubscribe, they simply click the link and the system will remove them.</p>
<p><a href="http://tipsandtech.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/1-4-2011-7-34-50-PM.png"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-213" title="1-4-2011 7-34-50 PM" src="http://tipsandtech.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/1-4-2011-7-34-50-PM.png" alt="" width="202" height="184" /></a>Another nice feature is that you can easily get the HTML code that you can embed on to your current website that allows visitors to signup for your newsletter on their own.</p>
<p>The menu options are fairly straight forward and not to complex.  Here is the menu;<img class="size-full wp-image-212 alignright" title="1-4-2011 7-56-38 PM" src="http://tipsandtech.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/1-4-2011-7-56-38-PM.png" alt="" width="305" height="250" /></p>
<p>Another cool feature was that is one of your reader &#8220;replies&#8221; to your email newsletter, you get an email notifying you of their response and keeps all of the replies in the TinyLetter system.</p>
<p>TinyLetter did have a few features I was looking for and didn&#8217;t find.  It would be great if they offered nice looking visual templates for your newsletters.  It does allow you to add a custom background, but I couldn&#8217;t get it to work during my testing.</p>
<p>If you are looking for a simple way for your website visitors to signup for regular contact from you by asking to receive your newsletter, and to easily keep in touch with your current contacts, TinyLetter might be a good solution for you.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
			<wfw:commentRss>http://tipsandtech.com/want-an-simple-online-newsletter-try-tiny-letter/feed/</wfw:commentRss>
		<slash:comments />
		</item>
		<item>
		<title>Removing Facebook clutter</title>
		<link>http://tipsandtech.com/removing-facebook-clutter/</link>
		<comments>http://tipsandtech.com/removing-facebook-clutter/#comments</comments>
		<pubDate>Mon, 20 Dec 2010 20:52:03 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>John</dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[Facebook]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[facebook]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[farmville]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[mafiawars]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://tipsandtech.com/?p=202</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[Are you tired of your Facebook friends asking for or offering you cows, chickens and guns?  One of the biggest reasons I hear from my business associates is that they don&#8217;t use Facebook because of all the clutter. Game developers have created many online games that let you play with and interact with your online [...]]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p></p><p><a href="http://tipsandtech.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/12/images-1.jpg"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-203" title="facebook cow" src="http://tipsandtech.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/12/images-1.jpg" alt="" width="184" height="175" /></a>Are you tired of your Facebook friends asking for or offering you cows, chickens and guns?  One of the biggest reasons I hear from my business associates is that they don&#8217;t use Facebook because of all the clutter.</p>
<p>Game developers have created many online games that let you play with and interact with your online Facebook friends. MafiaWars and Farmville are two of the most popular games out, and the bad thing is that they seem to take over your friend&#8217;s Facebook news feeds. Did you know that these notifications can easily be turned off?  Today, I&#8217;m going to show you how to turn these annoying notices off for good.</p>
<p>This is a fairly easy process.  It is so easy, I&#8217;m going to show you how to remove these notifications in 3 easy steps.</p>
<p>1.  Open your Facebook (that was easy!)</p>
<p>2. Read through your news feed until you find one of these notifications.  It could be Cafe World, Farmville, Cityville, QuizWhiz, Mafia Wars, or a number of other things that you see coming up on a regular basis.</p>
<p><a href="http://tipsandtech.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/12/Picture1.png"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-204" title="farmlist" src="http://tipsandtech.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/12/Picture1.png" alt="" width="531" height="597" /></a></p>
<p>3.  When you find one, move your mouse to the top right of the notification.  You will notice that a &#8220;X&#8221; appears.  Click on the &#8220;X&#8221; and you are give a few options.</p>
<p><a href="http://tipsandtech.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/12/12-20-2010-2-42-10-PM.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-205" title="12-20-2010 2-42-10 PM" src="http://tipsandtech.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/12/12-20-2010-2-42-10-PM.png" alt="" width="510" height="220" /></a></p>
<p>At this point, click &#8220;Hide all by &lt;name of the game&gt;,&#8221; and notifications from that game will never be seen again!</p>
<p><em>Note:  If you click &#8220;Hide all by &lt;your friends name&gt;, you will never see any posts by this person ever again, so be careful you click the correct selection!</em></p>
]]></content:encoded>
			<wfw:commentRss>http://tipsandtech.com/removing-facebook-clutter/feed/</wfw:commentRss>
		<slash:comments />
		</item>
		<item>
		<title>Tired of getting emails from Facebook?</title>
		<link>http://tipsandtech.com/tired-of-getting-emails-from-facebook/</link>
		<comments>http://tipsandtech.com/tired-of-getting-emails-from-facebook/#comments</comments>
		<pubDate>Wed, 15 Dec 2010 22:04:53 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>John</dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[Facebook]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Time Saving Tool]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[facebook]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://tipsandtech.com/?p=187</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[I had two agents ask me today, how do I stop getting all these emails from Facebook? I decided it must be the subject of a TipsAndTech.com article, because many people must have the same questions. By default, Facebook wants to email you a notification every time something happen in Facebook that relates to your [...]]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p></p><p><a href="http://tipsandtech.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/12/fb.jpg"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-188" title="fb" src="http://tipsandtech.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/12/fb.jpg" alt="" width="224" height="224" /></a>I had two agents ask me today, how do I stop getting all these emails from Facebook? I decided it must be the subject of a TipsAndTech.com article, because many people must have the same questions.</p>
<p>By default, Facebook wants to email you a notification every time something happen in Facebook that relates to your account.  The initial idea was to prompt you to go back into Facebook to see what someone wrote on your wall, commented about, see the photo they tagged you in, etc. Nowadays, visiting Facebook and checking your updates is about as common as checking your email account.</p>
<p>Today I&#8217;m going to show you how to turn those annoying email notifications off for good.  I will suggest that you keep just a few turned on, but we&#8217;ll save that for later.</p>
<p><img class="size-full wp-image-191 alignleft" title="12-15-2010 3-39-36 PM" src="http://tipsandtech.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/12/12-15-2010-3-39-36-PM.png" alt="" width="281" height="265" />Once you login to your Facebook, you should click the Account button at the top right of your Facebook page.  Then click on Account Settings.</p>
<p>You settings page will then be displayed.  From here you need to click the Notifications tab at the top.</p>
<p><a href="http://tipsandtech.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/12/12-15-2010-3-42-27-PM.png"><img class="size-full wp-image-192 alignnone" title="12-15-2010 3-42-27 PM" src="http://tipsandtech.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/12/12-15-2010-3-42-27-PM.png" alt="" width="272" height="121" /></a>Below, you will see two columns with checkbox options where you can select when you want to be notified and by which method, by email, or by text message.  <em>If the text message boxes are grayed out and not selectable, You can click on the Mobile tab at the top to set that option up.</em></p>
<p><a href="http://tipsandtech.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/12/12-15-2010-3-46-56-PM.png"><img class="size-full wp-image-194 alignright" title="12-15-2010 3-46-56 PM" src="http://tipsandtech.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/12/12-15-2010-3-46-56-PM.png" alt="" width="320" height="223" /></a>If you are frustrated by the number of emails you get from Facebook I suggest you uncheck all the boxes in the email column except for a select few.  I suggest you leave these few on for sure, and any others that you think are important.</p>
<ul>
<li>sends you a message</li>
<li>posts on your wall</li>
<li>tags me on their profile</li>
<li>tags you in a post</li>
<li>tags you in a photo</li>
<li>comments on a story on your wall</li>
<li>tags you at a place</li>
</ul>
<p>I think you should leave these options on, either as an email or a text message because these are your friends trying to engage with you directly.  Remember Facebook is about engaging with people.</p>
<p><strong>Once you have the checkboxes set, be sure to hit the Save button at the bottom of the page. </strong></p>
<p>Hopefully these tips help you control the amount of email you are receiving from Facebook.  If you think this was useful, please let me know in the comments  below!</p>
<ul>
<li>tags you in a video</li>
</ul>
]]></content:encoded>
			<wfw:commentRss>http://tipsandtech.com/tired-of-getting-emails-from-facebook/feed/</wfw:commentRss>
		<slash:comments />
		</item>
		<item>
		<title>Generate business leads with Google Docs</title>
		<link>http://tipsandtech.com/generate-business-leads-with-google-docs/</link>
		<comments>http://tipsandtech.com/generate-business-leads-with-google-docs/#comments</comments>
		<pubDate>Tue, 14 Dec 2010 21:42:36 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>John</dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[Marketing]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Prospecting]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Google Docs]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Lead Generation]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Online forms]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://tipsandtech.com/?p=176</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[You all know I am a fan of everything Google.  Today I am going to talk a little bit about Google Docs. Google Docs is a free online service that provides an online alternative to Microsoft Office.  It includes a word processor, a spreadsheet builder, a presentation builder, an online storage location, and a form [...]]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p></p><p><a href="http://tipsandtech.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/12/docs.jpg"><img class="alignright size-full wp-image-180" title="docs" src="http://tipsandtech.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/12/docs.jpg" alt="" width="240" height="180" /></a>You all know I am a fan of everything Google.  Today I am going to talk a little bit about <a href="http://docs.google.com/" target="_blank">Google Docs</a>.</p>
<p>Google Docs is a free online service that provides an online alternative to Microsoft Office.  It includes a word processor, a spreadsheet builder, a presentation builder, an online storage location, and a form builder.  Today we are going to talk about the form builder.</p>
<p>If you have a website, then hopefully you know that just having a website is not going to typically make you money.  Most agent websites out there today, are static brochure type websites that don&#8217;t encourage any interaction.  Call-to-action is the name of the game.  You must give them an excuse to engage with you by actually giving you their contact information for something in return.  An online form is the simplest way for them to share their information with you.</p>
<p><a href="http://tipsandtech.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/12/12-14-2010-3-16-01-PM.png"><img class="size-full wp-image-182 alignleft" title="12-14-2010 3-16-01 PM" src="http://tipsandtech.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/12/12-14-2010-3-16-01-PM.png" alt="" width="168" height="159" /></a>You&#8217;ve seen them and most likely filled an online form out to get some information a website promised you.  Now you will be able to create your own online form to generate potential clients.</p>
<p>The first step is how are you going to get people to actually fill the form out.  You must give them something compelling that they can&#8217;t get anywhere else more easily.  How about offer them a free report about a hot topic in your field?  How about offer them a free evaluation or estimate?  The ideas are endless.  Look at your business and ask yourself, what do people want that I can provide.  For my REALTOR® friends here are a few ideas&#8230;</p>
<ul>
<li>Create a free report titled &#8220;10 Mistakes home buyers make and how to avoid them!&#8221;</li>
<li>Offer a free list of foreclosed properties in your area.</li>
<li>Offer a free home evaluation or market study to potential sellers.</li>
</ul>
<p>What other things could you offer to your clients to encourage them to give you, &#8220;a salesperson&#8221;, their contact information?</p>
<p><em>Note: If you promise to give them a report or some kind of service, send them the information they asked for!</em></p>
<p>So now you just need to know how to create the form and get it out to the masses!  Well I don&#8217;t want to reinvent the wheel here.  <a href="http://210consulting.com/" target="_blank">Jeremy Blanton at 210 Consulting</a> has already written a great article and created a nice video on the process. You get the rest of the information here.</p>
<p><a href="http://210consulting.com/2010/12/10/using-google-docs-to-generate-leads/"><img class="size-full wp-image-183 alignnone" title="google docs for lead generation" src="http://tipsandtech.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/12/12-14-2010-3-32-05-PM.png" alt="" width="574" height="349" /></a></p>
]]></content:encoded>
